Process of Table 1 Replication

For the process of recreating table 1 of this paper, I separated the data into two separate matrices where matrix 1 had all of the tweets that were labeled false and the other matrix had all the tweets that were labeled true. Next, I identified the columns that matched the individual rows in the original feature column and then ran the ks.test function provided by R where each sample was from the same column but different matrices. (i.e. num_retweets from False and num_retweets from True) The thing that I chose to vary in this reproduction was the actual Kolmogorov Smirnov Test, in the paper the authors said they ran the actual test which I interpreted as them coding the test and running it but I just called an R function. I assumed that this didn’t matter and found that it didn’t because we got the same results.

I did the same for alternative for all of them, but they did a mix of l and g.
